title: For Sale:  Mosin Nagant M91 Rifle 1917
postcontent: Up for sale is a Tsarist M91 Mosin Nagant rifle. This is NOT the standard, dirt-cheap M91/30 rifle that everyone and their brother has for sale. Made at Tula in 1917, this is a WWI production Mosin and still retains its original Russian stock (many were refurbed and refitted post-WW1 by the Finnish military) and original, unmessed-with rear sight. All matching, import marked on the barrel. Bore is worn and dirty, but good rifling still remains. The action is somewhat rough to operate, although I suspect the bolt is the cause. I've tested this action with other M91 and 91/30 bolts and they are much smoother than the bolt that is matching to this rifle. I highly recommend having this rifle checked by a gunsmith before firing. It is over 100 years old and I am selling it as a collectible. Thank you!
